body.name: GAMDIAS ATX Mid Tower Gaming Computer PC Case with Side Tempered Glass, 4X 120mm ARGB Case Fans and Sync with 5V RGB Motherboard and Excellent Airflow
features: ONE CLICK. SYNC ALL: The gaming desktop case supports RGB connection to compatible motherboards in order to achieve system-wide lighting synchronization, making it easier to unite the case from chaos to calm
PANORAMIC TEMPERED GLASS: Showcase the inner beauty of your gaming pc system in full with a full-sized tempered glass cover with tool-free installation for ease of access
3+1 BUILT-IN ARGB FANS: The gaming chassis is well equipped with 4 built-in 120mm ARGB fans displayed in full by the mesh front panel and the tempered glass side panel
SLEEK Design with Mesh Front: AURA GC1 sports an airflow-focused mesh front panel with a sleek stealth black design to provide aesthetics and excellent airflow intake

Great Expandability for Your Gaming Rig.: With 2 x 3.5" or 1 x 2.5"+1 x 3.5"(HDD Cage) / 2 x 2.5" HDD Tray, USB 3.0 x1, USB 2.0 x2, HD Audio x1, LED Control x1. Furthermore, it supports different mobo from ATX, Micro-ATX, Mini-ITX . 7 PCIE slots allow you to fully utilize your motherboard.
body.description: The AURA GC2 is an affordable mid-tower case with an airflow-oriented design. Featuring a chamfered front panel with perforated air vents, 4 built-in ARGB fans, and a panoramic tempered glass side panel to show off the beauty of your build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wonderful little case for the price
reviews.reviewText: I have put together numerous computers - at least 20 - in the past. I needed an inexpensive case to put together a computer composed of spare parts that ended up being left over from another computer upgrade.The Gamdias case was able to fulfill the job perfectly. Yes, the metal is thin and you can bend it with your hands if you really tried. However, all the screw holes lined up well, and the layout and design of the case is very very simple, with virtually zero wasted space.I like how the power supply cables are all hidden by a shroud. The white color aesthetic is beautiful. The USB ports on the top of the case work great at USB 3, plugged in correctly to the motherboard. Even the toggle button to cycle through the different LED color options of the case fans works as advertised.I encountered zero problems with this case, and ended up with a result that far exceeded my expectation for an inexpensive case. The smoked glass and LED lighting gives this computer a whole new life. Wonderful little case!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sharp looking and feels pretty solid
reviews.reviewText: Trying to fit an ATX motherboard, two radiators, and a lot of cables in this was pretty tight. Despite my ridiculous hardware, it was still fairly easy to build in. No sharp edges to cut you, the panels fit decently, the threads were cut pretty clean, and everything lined up like it should. Running a 240mm raditor up top, and a 120mm at the very bottom of the front of the case. Do note that if you run a radiator at the bottom like I did, or a 360mm radiator, you'll need to put them both on the inner side of the front panel unlike the factory fans being on the outer side. The plastic panel that snaps on doesn't accommodate a fan in that position, unless you wanted to cut it with a dremel or something. The included fans don't have any way to adjust their speed as far as I'm aware, but they're not too loud. Noticeable at idle, but once my clapped RX480 gets going it'll drown out a jet taking off, so I honestly can't complain. They do move a good volume of air though, and the front panel design is decent for air flow. I've had no over heating issues. Would I put an RTX4090 in this case? No, but it probably wouldn't fit anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Budget Case For Sweet PC Gaming Builds
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I purchased the Zeus Gamdias White Talos E3 WH Tower for a budget flip that I wanted to do. This case worked out really great.Pros:- Inexpensive- Fresh, clean minimalistic look, excellent RGB from the included fans that can be controlled via the LED button on top of the case. Can cycle through a variety of colors and effects- Plenty of room between front glass and case for adequate cooling, included fans push air well. Noise is fairly isolated (not the best I've heard, not the worst, I'd say about average).- Tempered glass is easy to remove with thumbscrews as is most items on the case- Plenty of clearance for full ATX partsCons:- Case material is on the cheaper side (door, etc) but honestly this doesn't really matter unless you are banging around your tower on things. For this price point, it's good and it LOOKS good (does not look cheap). Pretty comparable to NZXT H510 series.- Cable Management on the back is solid and there are adequate cutouts to reach the motherboard. I was disappointed that they didn't use a completely solid shroud for the top of the PSU area as it does show some wiring and there isn't a lot of cable stow-away space at the bottom. I used the HD/SSD Bay for most of my loose cables that I couldn't zip-tie and the area around it for anything that wouldn't fit. Overall, as you can see from the pictures it still looks VERY clean, but that little bit extra is what you get from the premium cases. I also couldn't find an "easy" way to route the fan cables behind the back of the case.- PCI slot covers are rip-away, with no way to put them back on and not enough screws for all the bay slots included. So you may have some gaps back there if you install additional cards.TLDR: Happy I gave the Gamdias brand a shot, this is a very solid looking tower for this price point and certainly gives some of the big brands competition. This will end up in a happy gamer's home very soon. Highly recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: Good value case, check your dimensions though!
reviews.reviewText: So I bought this case for a MSI B550M pro VDH WiFi motherboard, alongside a 5600 CPU and a thermalright frost tower 120 CPU cooler, and a 5700xt. Everything fits-just.Make sure to check the dimensions, my GPU length was 155mm, the max for this case is 160mm, and the CPU cooler fits with about 5mm between the cooler and tempered glass.The 4 included fans attached to my JRainbow on the motherboard, it included a aRGB splitter, so the one I bought in preparation was not required. The led button on the top of case cycles through about 15 different profiles, such as solid colours, slow changing and also breathing effects. Will check if MSI support changing of colour within software when I've installed a OS.The back of the case has an okay amount of cable management space, with tie in points for cable ties (included with this case) and twisty ties, though the back case does bulge outwards a tiny bit due to my cables. There's also 1 slot for a SSD to be attached to at the back. The HDD bay next to where the PSU would be had to be unscrewed and removed as I put in a ATX PSU from a previous build, I believe a SFX PSU should fit with the HDD bay.Nice mesh filters top and bottom of the case, and the front has great airflow for cooling, a slit on the left and right, and mesh design too.Overall this case is great value for the price, having the 4 aRGB case fans included was always a nice bonus, I preferred the square design on the front, as opposed to be GC1 (which is more rounded). The front of the GC3 looks similar to the beQuiet 500dx but only had 1 fan included, so this design was for me.Fast delivery, bought for £45 early Jan 24.
La compré en black friday, salió barata y es muy bonita , amplia , y limpia , los ventiladores y los leds están muy bien y se nota que el socket no sufre de temperatura
